WEBVTT

00:08.008 --> 00:09.551
[crash]

00:09.634 --> 00:12.554
[John B] <i>There are only three kinds</i>
<i>of relationships in the animal kingdom.</i>

00:13.930 --> 00:15.765
<i>The first is commensalism.</i>

00:16.266 --> 00:19.185
<i>One example...</i>
<i>fish finding hiding spots in coral reefs.</i>

00:19.269 --> 00:21.896
<i>Fish profit,</i>
<i>but life for the coral doesn't change.</i>

00:24.232 --> 00:25.358
[thud]

00:25.442 --> 00:28.028
-[John B] <i>Then, there's mutualism...</i>
-What happened?

00:28.194 --> 00:30.530
<i>...a relationship where both animals</i>
<i>benefit from each other.</i>

00:30.613 --> 00:31.865
[thunder crashing]

00:31.948 --> 00:34.451
[John B] <i>The tricky thing about animals</i>
<i>is you don't always know</i>

00:34.534 --> 00:36.536
<i>what kind of relationship you're in.</i>

00:39.831 --> 00:42.000
<i>Which brings me</i>
<i>to relationship number three.</i>

00:43.835 --> 00:44.961
<i>The parasitic.</i>

00:56.222 --> 00:57.432
Welcome home, kid.

00:58.558 --> 01:00.060
[Sarah] <i>This is your room.</i>

01:01.394 --> 01:02.228
Whoa.

01:03.813 --> 01:05.190
It's not too shabby, huh?

01:05.815 --> 01:07.525
Yeah. Not too shabby at all.

01:08.193 --> 01:10.528
And my room is just upstairs,

01:10.612 --> 01:11.946
in case you were wondering.

01:12.030 --> 01:14.157
-Are you okay?
-Yeah. No, I'm good. I'm good. I got it.

01:14.240 --> 01:15.784
-[groans]
-[Sarah chuckles]

01:15.992 --> 01:17.744
-But I have to warn you...
-Uh-oh.

01:17.827 --> 01:18.661
...I sleepwalk.

01:19.746 --> 01:22.791
-[John B sighs]
-[chuckles] So if I show up in your room

01:22.874 --> 01:25.335
-in the middle of the night--
-You just want me to roll with it?

01:26.002 --> 01:26.836
Yeah, maybe.

01:28.338 --> 01:30.256
[Ward] Sarah Elizabeth Cameron!

01:31.216 --> 01:33.760
You've already broken the first rule.
What is the first rule?

01:33.843 --> 01:35.178
Stay out of each other's rooms.

01:35.261 --> 01:37.722
All right, seriously.
Picture that as a boundary.

01:37.806 --> 01:39.808
This is like a minefield.

01:39.891 --> 01:41.142
-Yes, sir?
-Yes, sir.

01:41.226 --> 01:43.353
-[Ward] Yes, sir, John B?
-Uh, yes, sir. Yeah.

01:43.436 --> 01:44.354
All right.

01:44.813 --> 01:47.607
Sarah, can you give me and the new inmate
a quick minute here?

01:48.817 --> 01:49.734
Please be nice.

01:49.818 --> 01:50.693
I'll be nice.

01:51.945 --> 01:53.113
How you doin'? How's the arm?

01:53.613 --> 01:55.073
-Uh, better.
-[Ward] You're lucky.

01:55.156 --> 01:56.825
Fall any other way,
you don't hit that sand,

01:56.908 --> 01:58.868
you could've broken both your legs
and your back.

01:58.952 --> 02:00.328
[John B] Yeah, I'm super lucky.

02:00.411 --> 02:03.289
I just wanna say thank you
for sticking up to DCS for me.

02:03.373 --> 02:06.793
Don't even think about it.
Happy to do it. One other thing. Um...

02:08.753 --> 02:10.338
Last night, Sarah was in my office,

02:10.421 --> 02:14.008
and she was getting a map,
and she said it was for you, and...

02:15.802 --> 02:17.512
I'm sorry, but I just have to ask.

02:17.595 --> 02:21.224
You're not chasin' after pots of gold
like your old man, are you, John B?

02:27.814 --> 02:32.402
Look, Mr. C, uh... Sarah just told me
you guys had some cool old maps.

02:32.485 --> 02:33.570
Mm-hm.

02:34.154 --> 02:37.699
I'm kind of a history buff myself,
and, uh... [chuckles]

02:37.782 --> 02:39.951
...that, I guess, I got from my dad, so...

02:44.539 --> 02:45.540
That makes sense.

02:47.792 --> 02:51.296
Anyway, uh... take it easy
the next couple days, all right?

02:51.379 --> 02:53.298
-[John B] Absolutely.
-You've been through a lot.

03:16.696 --> 03:18.656
I'm sorry. You're staying where?

03:19.115 --> 03:19.991
Tannyhill.

03:20.658 --> 03:22.577
So you're living with Sarah Cameron.

03:23.536 --> 03:25.622
Okay, look, the only reason
I'm living there

03:25.705 --> 03:27.874
is because her dad bailed me out, right?

03:27.957 --> 03:30.418
And it's way better than foster care,
which, by the way,

03:30.501 --> 03:32.420
is where I was about to go
if Ward didn't--

03:32.503 --> 03:34.547
Hey, so do you have a membership
to the clubs now?

03:34.631 --> 03:35.798
I don't know, Pope.

03:36.507 --> 03:39.093
What about those golf carts
they drive around? You get one of them?

03:39.177 --> 03:42.180
Does it come with a sweater-vest,
or do you have to buy one on your own?

03:42.263 --> 03:43.473
Look, you promised.

03:43.556 --> 03:45.058
You said you weren't with her.

03:45.642 --> 03:47.227
Bro, just own it. She got you.

03:48.019 --> 03:50.480
Look, if you wanna hang out with her,
that's fine.

03:50.813 --> 03:53.608
But I'm letting you know now
that I'm not doing anything with Sarah.

03:53.691 --> 03:55.151
Do you guys see her here?

03:55.235 --> 03:58.154
No, right. Okay.
A little focus would be fantastic.

03:58.905 --> 03:59.948
We've got the map, right?

04:00.031 --> 04:02.408
It's out of whack 'cause the guy
was ganja'd when he drew it.

04:02.825 --> 04:04.369
It's 'cause the coast has changed.

04:04.452 --> 04:06.996
[Pope] So we just have to look
for landmarks that haven't changed.

04:07.956 --> 04:09.249
What about the old forts?

04:09.916 --> 04:10.959
Battery Jasper.

04:16.047 --> 04:17.548
We're in Battery, right here.

04:18.383 --> 04:22.720
So if this is parcel nine,
then it's somewhere northeast of here.

04:22.804 --> 04:24.305
-[Kie] Somehwere there.
-[Pope] Right.

04:24.389 --> 04:27.267
Over there? Guy's, that's not Tannyhill,
that's a subdivision.

04:27.350 --> 04:29.018
Tannyhill Plantation
was the entire island.

04:29.102 --> 04:31.229
It got sold into smaller pieces over time.

04:32.772 --> 04:35.275
[Pope] So we're just looking
for an old stone wall.

04:35.358 --> 04:37.819
-Okay, so the road should split up here.
-[John B] Okay.

04:37.902 --> 04:39.612
All right. You're gonna take a left.

04:43.032 --> 04:44.826
[JJ] That looks like a stone wall to me.

04:45.827 --> 04:46.744
This is it.

04:47.245 --> 04:49.706
-[car doors open]
-[John B] Not the Crain house.

04:51.749 --> 04:53.876
-Are you kidding me?
-[car doors close]

04:53.960 --> 04:55.044
Worst-case scenario.

04:55.128 --> 04:56.421
Why'd it have to be here...

04:57.213 --> 04:58.256
of all places?

04:58.339 --> 05:01.759
I heard that Mrs. Crain
buried her husband's head on the property.

05:03.970 --> 05:05.430
[Peterkin] <i>Domestic disturbance,</i>

05:06.556 --> 05:08.057
potential home invasion.

05:08.141 --> 05:09.267
Reports had it wrong.

05:09.976 --> 05:11.811
Nobody invaded anybody.

05:11.894 --> 05:13.313
[Peterkin] Two men were here, Lana.

05:13.396 --> 05:15.231
The only questions I have
is why were they here,

05:15.315 --> 05:16.733
and why are you protecting them?

05:18.609 --> 05:21.154
You mean to tell me
you ripped the front door off its hinges?

05:21.237 --> 05:23.531
[Lana] I was upset.
I had to break something.

05:23.614 --> 05:26.451
-Grief does powerful things.
-[Peterkin] Not that powerful.

05:28.036 --> 05:31.122
I got the GPS coordinates
off Scooter's Grady-White.

05:31.664 --> 05:34.208
I mapped out the route
he took that last day. You mind?

05:35.126 --> 05:37.420
Wanna know where he went? It's curious.

05:37.795 --> 05:40.465
On the day of the hurricane,
when he should've been here with you,

05:40.548 --> 05:42.675
he was riskin' his life,
goin' to an uninhabited island

05:42.759 --> 05:44.177
30 miles offshore.

05:45.261 --> 05:46.471
Now, Scooter...

05:47.347 --> 05:49.182
he wasn't a stupid man.

05:49.265 --> 05:52.226
Why he out in open water
on the day of the storm?

05:56.522 --> 05:57.940
If you're afraid of somebody,

05:58.816 --> 06:00.443
-I can protect you.
-[sighs]

06:00.526 --> 06:02.236
I told you, I don't know anything.

06:05.823 --> 06:07.867
[motorbike engine running]

06:07.950 --> 06:11.204
[sniffs, sighs]

06:11.287 --> 06:13.206
[Barry, loudly] You gonna give me a bump,
big boy?

06:13.581 --> 06:15.583
Man, check out this place, though, huh?

06:15.666 --> 06:17.627
-[Rafe] Hey, Barry. Barry. Hey, man.
-It's fancy!

06:18.211 --> 06:19.921
It's a nice place to live!

06:20.004 --> 06:22.131
-[quietly] I don't have your money.
-[Barry] Mm-hm.

06:22.215 --> 06:24.717
All right? Uh-- you shouldn't be here now.
What are you doing?

06:24.801 --> 06:27.595
-I'm right here. You wanna know why?
-Give me till the weekend, okay?

06:27.678 --> 06:29.680
All I-- all I need you to do
is front me more coke.

06:29.764 --> 06:31.808
-Mm-hm. Yeah.
-[Rafe] I got a guy coming this weekend.

06:31.891 --> 06:33.768
-It's cool, right?
-Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

06:33.851 --> 06:35.937
How come you got
all this nice shit, though?

06:36.020 --> 06:37.438
-Can you tell me that?
-[sniffs]

06:37.522 --> 06:40.274
You ain't got my money,
but you got all this nice shit.

06:40.358 --> 06:41.526
-Man, yeah, just...
-Hm? Hm?

06:41.609 --> 06:43.736
-Hey, chill, chill! All right-- Hey!
-Come here!

06:43.820 --> 06:46.322
-Hey! Get off! What're you doing? Hey!
-[grunting]

06:46.406 --> 06:48.491
-[skin sizzling]
-[Barry] Put that on there. Yeah!

06:48.574 --> 06:50.701
-Hey! Shit! Stop, stop, stop, stop!
-That's it!

06:50.785 --> 06:53.496
-That's it, you little bitch!
-Okay, stop, stop! Okay, chill, man.

06:53.579 --> 06:55.957
-[groaning]
-[Barry] How's that feel, baby boy?

06:56.541 --> 06:58.835
That's just the coming attractions,
big boy.

06:59.836 --> 07:00.670
[Rafe groaning]

07:00.753 --> 07:03.214
Consider this shit right here
your down payment.

07:04.173 --> 07:05.883
-You got three days.
-[Rafe moaning]

07:07.844 --> 07:09.387
[revs engine]

07:10.763 --> 07:11.848
[groans]

07:14.642 --> 07:16.644
[continues moaning]

07:22.108 --> 07:24.193
[Kie] Look, you guys know
whose house this is, right?

07:24.277 --> 07:25.236
[JJ] Oh, yeah. No, I do.

07:25.319 --> 07:27.572
Honestly, I don't really believe
the stories of this place.

07:27.655 --> 07:29.031
-[Pope] Shh.
-What?

07:30.450 --> 07:31.826
Which stories did you hear?

07:32.326 --> 07:35.037
The one where she killed her husband
with an axe

07:35.121 --> 07:37.123
and that she's been holed up ever since.

07:37.665 --> 07:39.667
On certain nights,
when the moon is full...

07:40.376 --> 07:41.544
you can see her in the window!

07:41.627 --> 07:43.963
-No, it's not funny, 'cause it's all true.
-Waah!

07:44.046 --> 07:47.425
I swear to God, guys, this is all real.
I knew Hollis. Jeez!

07:47.508 --> 07:49.635
-Wait, you knew Hollis Crain?
-Yeah, dude.

07:49.719 --> 07:51.637
Dude, how do you know Hollis Crain?

07:51.721 --> 07:54.599
She was my babysitter, man.
She told me all about it.

07:54.682 --> 07:57.310
Told me the truth... about her mother

07:57.768 --> 07:59.353
and what happened in this house.

08:00.313 --> 08:04.108
So as a kid, she heard all the stories
that her mother killed her father,<i> </i>and...

08:04.192 --> 08:05.776
she was a murderer and all.

08:05.860 --> 08:07.153
Hollis didn't believe it.

08:08.154 --> 08:10.239
-Until that night.
-What night?

08:11.657 --> 08:12.867
It all came back to her.

08:16.287 --> 08:19.999
When Hollis was six years old,
she heard her parents arguing downstairs.

08:20.583 --> 08:23.961
So she goes downstairs to see her mom
washing her hands in a sink...

08:24.962 --> 08:26.923
full of blood.

08:28.674 --> 08:30.760
Her mother just says
that she cut her finger.

08:31.677 --> 08:33.971
The next morning,
she says her father and her split up.

08:34.847 --> 08:36.390
But then, Hollis noticed something.

08:36.891 --> 08:39.519
Her mother going
into the parlor constantly,

08:40.019 --> 08:43.105
in and out and in and out
with plastic bags.

08:43.189 --> 08:45.942
Weeks pass,
and Hollis decides to use the outhouse.

08:46.025 --> 08:48.653
And as she's using it, she looks down,

08:48.736 --> 08:51.030
and there, in the outhouse,

08:51.739 --> 08:55.368
is her father's head,
looking straight back at her.

08:55.451 --> 08:57.078
God, you are so full of shit.

08:57.161 --> 08:58.496
Dude, I swear to God, man.

08:58.579 --> 09:00.581
-Did she call the police?
-She didn't have time.

09:00.665 --> 09:02.333
-[Pope] We can't do this--
-Wait! Dude!

09:02.416 --> 09:03.417
What?

09:05.336 --> 09:08.297
You sure you wanna do this?
She's an axe murderer. You got a cast on.

09:08.381 --> 09:10.967
I don't give a shit
if she's an axe murderer, okay?

09:11.551 --> 09:14.929
I got nothin' to lose, right?
You comin' or what?

09:16.389 --> 09:17.390
[Kie] Come on.

09:22.270 --> 09:23.646
[whispers] Hey, come on. Come here.

09:24.397 --> 09:27.358
So here's the plan. We need to look
for the wheat near the water

09:27.441 --> 09:28.943
like it said in Denmark's letter.

09:29.443 --> 09:32.446
Okay, like, what kind of water?
Like, pond water?

09:32.530 --> 09:33.739
[chuckles] Bong water?

09:33.823 --> 09:36.534
No. It--
it just said look for water, okay?

09:37.368 --> 09:39.245
That's the shittiest secret message ever.

09:41.205 --> 09:44.500
You wanna complain a little more, Kie?
Nobody said it was gonna be easy.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.919
I'll search the northeast quadrant,
you search the northwest.

09:47.336 --> 09:48.963
The decapitation quadrant.

09:51.007 --> 09:53.009
-[rustling]
-[bird calls]

10:01.934 --> 10:03.978
[birds squawking]

10:12.278 --> 10:13.946
[woodpecker drilling]

10:14.363 --> 10:18.117
[quietly] Hey, psst! Hey, come on.
It's the only place we haven't looked.

10:18.701 --> 10:19.577
[rustling]

10:19.660 --> 10:21.203
-[wings flapping]
-[JJ] Oh, shit...

10:24.123 --> 10:24.957
Here we go.

10:37.928 --> 10:39.180
[sighs]

10:43.893 --> 10:48.022
<i>♪ Down came Mrs. Crain</i>
<i>And cut off all our heads ♪</i>

10:48.105 --> 10:50.858
<i>♪ Up came the sun</i>
<i>And dried up all the blood ♪</i>

10:50.941 --> 10:53.152
[Pope] Can you stop?

10:53.653 --> 10:55.488
-[creaking]
-[Kie gasps]

10:58.074 --> 10:59.241
See any water?

11:01.160 --> 11:02.787
[mosquito buzzing]

11:06.916 --> 11:08.167
[Kie] Another dead end?

11:10.544 --> 11:12.588
[JJ] There's not even water on the pipes.

11:13.255 --> 11:14.382
There's no water here.

11:14.465 --> 11:18.386
-Not a dropamino.
-[Kie] Know why we didn't find it?

11:19.136 --> 11:20.096
Bad karma.

11:20.179 --> 11:21.389
Oh, God. Here we go.

11:21.472 --> 11:23.307
You know, we had a good thing going.

11:23.724 --> 11:27.186
And then you decide to rope in Barbie,
and now the trail's gone dry.

11:27.269 --> 11:28.437
Coincidence? Probably not.

11:28.521 --> 11:30.856
This is exactly why
I didn't wanna tell you about Sarah.

11:30.940 --> 11:31.857
-[Kie] Yeah?
-Yeah.

11:31.941 --> 11:34.276
-What the hell's the deal with you two?
-Nothing.

11:34.360 --> 11:37.113
Nothing? Is it because I kissed you?
Is that the problem?

11:37.196 --> 11:38.614
-[Pope] Oh!
-[JJ] Oh, shit!

11:38.698 --> 11:40.282
-That echoed, dude!
-Stop treating me

11:40.366 --> 11:42.827
like I'm some girl
that's obsessed with you

11:42.910 --> 11:45.621
instead of your best friend
who's actually trying to look out for you.

11:45.705 --> 11:46.997
Did you, uh... hit me?

11:47.081 --> 11:49.125
-Skeeter.
-[John B] Skeeter?

11:49.208 --> 11:50.710
-Yeah, you see it?
-[John B] Yeah.

11:50.793 --> 11:51.919
-[JJ] Oh, hey!
-[Pope] Okay...

11:52.002 --> 11:53.170
-[JJ] No--
-Where's your proof?

11:54.588 --> 11:55.423
Skeeter.

11:55.840 --> 11:58.843
-Yeah? There was probably one right there.
-There's one right there.

11:58.926 --> 12:00.428
-[Kie] Really? You saw that?
-[Pope] Sh!

12:00.511 --> 12:02.138
-On your forehead.
-You're dead. That's it.

12:02.221 --> 12:03.973
Today's the day that you die.

12:04.056 --> 12:05.599
-[Pope] Jesus.
-Today's your funeral.

12:05.683 --> 12:07.184
-[mosquito buzzes]
-[Kie] One bandito.

12:07.268 --> 12:09.395
-These things are a freakin' swarm!
-[Kie] You see this?

12:09.478 --> 12:10.646
[JJ] Hey, sh! Keep it down!

12:10.730 --> 12:12.690
-[Kie chuckles]
-[John B] You know how this ends.

12:12.773 --> 12:14.650
Why are there so many mosquitoes
in a basement?

12:14.734 --> 12:18.154
[JJ] Dude. I know, seriously.
Tiny vampire bats, just leave me alone.

12:20.406 --> 12:23.951
Oh, my gosh! Okay, can we leave?
'Cause I'm already itchin' to leave.

12:24.034 --> 12:25.286
Hah? Punny.

12:27.079 --> 12:29.623
[John B groans] All right... Ow!

12:29.707 --> 12:31.751
I just found
Mrs. Crain's voodoo doll, guys.

12:32.251 --> 12:33.794
[Kie giggling] Oh, shit.

12:35.087 --> 12:37.339
[JJ] All right, can we leave this?
'Cause this is getting--

12:37.423 --> 12:38.924
[water splashes, echoes]

12:39.008 --> 12:40.676
[Kie] Skeeter, for real.

12:42.178 --> 12:43.554
-Hey, guys.
-[JJ] Hey, Pope!

12:43.637 --> 12:44.638
-[John B] Oh!
-[Kie] Sh!

12:44.722 --> 12:46.390
-Hey. Help me move this.
-Sh! Um...

12:46.474 --> 12:48.476
-[whispers] Help me move this.
-Okay, just... quiet.

12:49.310 --> 12:50.394
-[JJ] All right.
-[Pope] Hey.

12:51.687 --> 12:52.563
[John B] Sh!

12:53.898 --> 12:56.317
-[Kie] Guys! Guys!
-[Pope] Guys. I know. Yeah. Yeah. Sh, sh.

12:56.400 --> 12:57.985
[Kie] She's probably right upstairs.

13:10.915 --> 13:12.374
[Pope] Well, well, well.

13:12.458 --> 13:13.709
That was a good dad joke.

13:19.840 --> 13:22.009
They built this part of the house
right over it.

13:22.092 --> 13:24.512
-This is where she hid the bodies.
-Oh, dude, come on.

13:24.595 --> 13:25.888
-Stop.
-No, I'm dead serious.

13:25.971 --> 13:26.806
-Stop it!
-Hey, hey.

13:26.889 --> 13:29.642
-It was never an outhouse.
-She probably doesn't even know it's here.

13:30.100 --> 13:30.976
So...

13:32.686 --> 13:33.687
we found water.

13:33.771 --> 13:35.523
We're gonna need a really big rope.

13:43.072 --> 13:44.281
[door closes]

13:45.282 --> 13:46.116
[Topper] Hey.

13:49.370 --> 13:51.539
Hey, how's John B?
Is he-- is he doin' all right?

13:52.957 --> 13:55.543
-Like you give a shit.
-[Topper] You realize I did not push him.

13:55.626 --> 13:57.545
-He lost his balance and fell.
-[Sarah] Don't lie.

13:57.628 --> 14:00.798
-He fell against the rail. Not my fault.
-[Sarah] That is messed up.

14:00.881 --> 14:02.424
[scoffs]

14:03.509 --> 14:05.511
[Topper] You forget about us, like--

14:05.594 --> 14:07.888
Midsummers was supposed to be
our-- our coming-out party.

14:07.972 --> 14:09.890
That was supposed to be
something special, right?

14:09.974 --> 14:12.184
What does it matter, Topper?
We're in high school.

14:12.268 --> 14:13.811
It's not like we're getting married.

14:13.894 --> 14:15.980
I don't care if we're in high school!
I love you!

14:16.063 --> 14:18.315
-[Sarah] No, you don't, Topper!
-I love you!

14:18.899 --> 14:20.442
You love the idea of me.

14:20.526 --> 14:22.361
